# Kyle Lo | Semantic Scholar

[

## SciBERT: A Pretrained Language Model for Scientific Text

](/paper/SciBERT%3A-A-Pretrained-Language-Model-for-Scientific-Beltagy-Lo/156d217b0a911af97fa1b5a71dc909ccef7a8028)

[Iz Beltagy](/author/Iz-Beltagy/46181066)[Kyle Lo](/author/Kyle-Lo/46258841)[Arman Cohan](/author/Arman-Cohan/2527954)

Computer Science, Biology

-   1 March 2019

SciBERT leverages unsupervised pretraining on a large multi-domain corpus of scientific publications to improve performance on downstream scientific NLP tasks and demonstrates statistically significant improvements over BERT.

[

## Don’t Stop Pretraining: Adapt Language Models to Domains and Tasks

](/paper/Don%E2%80%99t-Stop-Pretraining%3A-Adapt-Language-Models-to-Gururangan-Marasovi%C4%87/e816f788767eec6a8ef0ea9eddd0e902435d4271)

[Suchin Gururangan](/author/Suchin-Gururangan/40895369)[Ana Marasović](/author/Ana-Marasovi%C4%87/3451494) [Noah A. Smith](/author/Noah-A.-Smith/144365875)

Computer Science

-   23 April 2020

It is consistently found that multi-phase adaptive pretraining offers large gains in task performance, and it is shown that adapting to a task corpus augmented using simple data selection strategies is an effective alternative, especially when resources for domain-adaptive pretraining might be unavailable.

[

## BLOOM: A 176B-Parameter Open-Access Multilingual Language Model

](/paper/BLOOM%3A-A-176B-Parameter-Open-Access-Multilingual-Scao-Fan/964bd39b546f0f6625ff3b9ef1083f797807ef2e)

[Teven Le Scao](/author/Teven-Le-Scao/1379806208)[Angela Fan](/author/Angela-Fan/144270981) [Thomas Wolf](/author/Thomas-Wolf/50335211)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   9 November 2022

BLOOM is a 176B-parameter open-access language model designed and built thanks to a collaboration of hundreds of researchers and achieves competitive performance on a wide variety of benchmarks, with stronger results after undergoing multitask prompted finetuning.

[

## CORD-19: The Covid-19 Open Research Dataset

](/paper/CORD-19%3A-The-Covid-19-Open-Research-Dataset-Wang-Lo/bc411487f305e451d7485e53202ec241fcc97d3b)

[Lucy Lu Wang](/author/Lucy-Lu-Wang/31860505)[Kyle Lo](/author/Kyle-Lo/46258841) [Sebastian Kohlmeier](/author/Sebastian-Kohlmeier/41018147)

Computer Science, Medicine

NLPCOVID19

-   22 April 2020

The mechanics of dataset construction are described, highlighting challenges and key design decisions, an overview of how CORD-19 has been used, and several shared tasks built around the dataset are described.

[

## S2ORC: The Semantic Scholar Open Research Corpus

](/paper/S2ORC%3A-The-Semantic-Scholar-Open-Research-Corpus-Lo-Wang/5c5751d45e298cea054f32b392c12c61027d2fe7)

In S2ORC, a large corpus of 81.1M English-language academic papers spanning many academic disciplines is introduced, which is expected to facilitate research and development of tools and tasks for text mining over academic text.

## OLMo: Accelerating the Science of Language Models

](/paper/OLMo%3A-Accelerating-the-Science-of-Language-Models-Groeneveld-Beltagy/ac45bbf9940512d9d686cf8cd3a95969bc313570)

[Dirk Groeneveld](/author/Dirk-Groeneveld/3458736)[Iz Beltagy](/author/Iz-Beltagy/2260133345) [Hanna Hajishirzi](/author/Hanna-Hajishirzi/2264251662)

## A Dataset of Information-Seeking Questions and Answers Anchored in Research Papers

](/paper/A-Dataset-of-Information-Seeking-Questions-and-in-Dasigi-Lo/4e3935ef7da6bcbb202ec7f8b285c313cadcd044)

[Pradeep Dasigi](/author/Pradeep-Dasigi/2697425)[Kyle Lo](/author/Kyle-Lo/46258841)[Iz Beltagy](/author/Iz-Beltagy/46181066)[Arman Cohan](/author/Arman-Cohan/2527954)[Noah A. Smith](/author/Noah-A.-Smith/144365875)[Matt Gardner](/author/Matt-Gardner/40642935)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   7 May 2021

Qasper is presented, a dataset of 5049 questions over 1585 Natural Language Processing papers that is designed to facilitate document-grounded, information-seeking QA, and finds that existing models that do well on other QA tasks do not perform well on answering these questions.
